caption: The sandwiches are AMAZING. Went for the first time today with my gluten free daughter, we will definitely be back!
My FAVORITE! Though, I wish they would bring back the pastries.
Popular spot serving gluten and dairy free baked goodies and sandwiches.
Best go bagels I’ve had. Great selection and friendly staff!

Mediocre at best. Sandwiches were decent but the baked goods were disappointing. It's a covid-nightmare. If you order online, you still have to stand in line up against too many strangers to safely fit inside waiting for them all to order. And several things in our order were missing.
Excellent vegan, soy free options!
I love their baked goods, they have a great selection here and the service is one of a kind too
Love their baked goods, they’re so delicious and the service staff are awesome too. This place is a must if you’re in the area
Great bagels! The croissants were only good fresh, not frozen. But a great find otherwise.
Amazing. Completely Celiac safe!

I love this place! We live out in South riding, VA but I still try to make it here a few times a year. Everything is delicious and it's nice to be gluten and dairy free and, for once, walk in and know what's in everything you plan to eat. I haven't tried one thing that isn't so good, and alot of my family can't tell the difference between these treats and their gluten, dairy-full counterparts. Highly recommend!
$3/bagel here is what you get
This place is amazing 👏 everything is delicious!!

As a newly gluten-free eater, I was excited to try my first all GF bakery. My partner and I grabbed sandwiches and pastries here and both were so yummy! A quaint little bakery with a variety of options and all are delicious!
Friendly and responsive service!
Gluten-free Delicious croissants! Love the chocolate and the ham and cheese! The cinnamon roll is.also wonderful. Heat it up!

Our favorite Gluten Free spot! Highly recommend this place! We always make sure to stock up on the many wonderful items these folks produce! Everything from a humble bagel with cream cheese all the way up to a big ol cake are done with care and are just as delicious as their non GF counterparts! Help us keep these fine people in business and enjoy their seriously excellent food in the process!
My girlfriend was so thrilled by this place we went twice in the same day

What a joke, it looks like an 8 year old wrote happy birthday on the cake we ordered. We will never be ordering from this bakery again - I could have done a better job writing with my feet-  I wish I could attach a photo for y’all to see but my phone won’t let me (added to their photos) 😂😂😂 looks like my cat tried to bake a cake

LOVE this place. Best gluten-free bagels I’ve every had. They taste like real bagels, which was so exciting after trying every other GF bagel. The croissant is also amazing, I’m so impressed that they can make such good GF baked goods!!! Highly recommend! :)
Best gluten free bakery for miles!
The best place for gluten free bread and chocolate croissant! The challah bread is quite amazing!
Very good!!
This is my favorite little bake shop. Everything here taste freaking amazing and fresh out the oven.
Friendly staff, pretty good breakfast sandwiches but nothing special. The energy bites were good too. A little pricey for the serving size.
Awesome as always, friendly, great food and service.

100% gluten free!!! Woohoo. Everything is labeled wonderfully.  I would have liked top see the allergen menu online in case I wanted delivery.  I wish they had a few more vegan options, but the options they had were delicious.  I cannot wait to return.  :)

I went here today and got the 18th st sandwich (BLT with herb mayo) on a toasted roll and it was honestly one of the BEST sandwiches of my life. Absolutely perfect!! The woman working there was so kind. Rise bakery is one of my favorite gf bakeries ever and I always make it a point to go there when I come to DC. I wish I could give this place more than 5 stars. 💛💛💛

If you are Gluten Free, I HIGHLY recommend picking up a handful of goodies from this wonderful shop!!! I recently picked up cupcakes and two types of croissants. She said she has never had croissants that are as good as these! Everything is fairly priced, so I highly recommend stopping by!!
As person having celiac, this place is the safest place for me eat and the most delicious options. My only wish, they were in my backyard!

I bring all of my gluten free friends here and they can’t get enough of it. One friend was almost in tears eating their Carrot cake cupcake for the first time since her Celiac diagnosis. A good option for those with food restrictions.
Great little 100% gluten free bakery. Charming place and really friendly staff in a nice area. Must visit if you need to stay away from gluten.
Gluten free for the win!

Awesome and very yummy Vegan chocolate chip cookies! :) I think they changed the recipe lately. The cookies used to be smaller and more crisp. Now they are softer and larger. I liked the change. I do wish they had more Vegan options though!
Best pastries!
Excellent.

My wife and I decided to try this place given our need for a gluten free diet. The store also has a sign saying that they have vegan options, soy free, etc.; but nothing is labeled to help a customer know whether something is gluten free, vegan, soy free, or otherwise. For a place that is supposed to be conscientious of peoples allergies (gluten intolerance, etc.), it's hard to believe that it lacks any kind of nutritional information.  Customer service was totally lacking. We ordered several pastries and ate in the store. After 30 minutes in the store not once did an employee greet or say goodbye to a customer. Greeting customers and making them feel welcomed and invited is the corner stone of any business. As for the pastires, we found them to be overpriced and extremely dry. I would not recommend this bakery for those truly interested in high quality gluten free options.

Decent GF bakery. Had a few items that were also dairy free, like the banana nut bread (a little dry and light on flavor) and what I believe was a carrot cupcake (pretty good). There was also a DF chocolate cake slice that I did not try. Only the avocado toast can be DF from their kitchen. All in all, it has options for those who have food restrictions beyond GF but was not worth traveling across the city for me.
My absolute favorite gluten free bakery. I have driven two hours out of my way just to get some of their croissants.

I tried several items, but they tasted bland to me.  I think the Superfood bread, chocolate croissant, pretzel, cinnamon bun, and carrot cake were 2/5. The brioche bread was slightly better but just ok, 3/5.  The store itself was small but pleasant. The employees were quick and courteous. But I don't plan on trying any more items off of the menu, because I felt consistently disappointed by the food itself.

I love this place. My favorite location to pamper myself with yummies. Everything is gluten free and they have other allergy safe treats as well. The best part is you will never know it because everything tastes so good. Absolutely worth it.
Croissant's that have nothing in common with real croissants but as its 'Gluten-free' at least you pay a small fortune for it.
Great gluten free bakery. Lots of options

This place is quite a mixed bag.  The scones are amazing, the ham and cheese croissant is good but has the faint tang of too much baking powder, and the nutella brownie is just okay.  The staff was very brusque.

Baker said they put in 30g of sodium per loaf. That's about 300% daily intake... Very high. That's disappointing.  If you have sodium concerns, don't recommend this place. I checked and harmony bakery in Baltimore does no Sodium custom orders for gluten free bread.

Stopped in here on a whim--I find it tough to pass by any sign with the word "bakery" on it. Super cute gluten-free bakery with lots of nice choices. If the chocolate cake is representative of their output, you will be happy you stopped by! Delicious and moist. The employees were just as sweet as the treats!!
Wonderful service..gluton free bagels, breads pies
Quiet little shop with great staff and delicious baked goods! The everything bagel was phenomenal!
Worth taking the time to hit this gem of a place.  Everything was so good.  The treats, the avocado toast.  GF person's dream come true!
Amazing food! Such great service as well. Make a point to get here.
Great bakery but limited seating. Bagels = Yum!
OH MY GIDDY AUNT! Rise Bakery rocks at gf yummy baked goods!!!!!

Okay so I was really excited to try this place but I can't help but feel unwelcomed by customer service. I've gone here twice, and coming from California, I can give their croissants and breads an amazing gluten free stamp but their pastries definitely taste gluten free and chalky, mastering GF means more than getting it to stick. With all being said, I am reluctant to go back. 1 star for the croissants. Another for the brioche. But -3 stars for customer service and flavor. This place would be amazing if the employees were more welcoming of all walks of life.
Excellent small bakery, especially for those with food allergies. All items are clearly marked, saving you from having to check ingredients. Plus, the cupcakes are great!

I walked past this bakery one day and was really excited because I saw it said "gluten free" on the outside. My mom is gluten free and loves dessert so I wanted to surprise her with something. I bought a piece of the flourless chocolate cake and a carrot cake cupcake. My mom - who LOVES dessert and is VERY content with almost anything, i.e. easy to please - said the chocolate cake was flavorless and not very sweet.  The next day she tried the carrot cake cupcake and said it was quote "awful" and as flavorless as the chocolate one, and she didn't taste any spices like you would expect in carrot cake. She only ate half of the cupcake. My mother does not NOT finish dessert. So it had to be pretty bad for her to only eat half.  Overall I am very disappointed. My mom did not enjoy either item and I bought them thinking it would be a nice treat for her.
slow service, but the food is amazing - havent had a cinnamon roll, croissant or a everything bagel is over 8 years. it was so good.
Ordered a chocolate birthday cake for my wife who has celiac disease and it was among the better cakes I've had (gluten free or not).
Pretty slow and nonchalant service ... Good pastries!
Our company ordered 2 gluten-free chocolate cakes for our CEO’s birthday and they were out of this world!! Really yummy!! The whole office was so impressed!
Go here for the chocolate croissant and cinnamon roll!  Gluten free baking isn't airy but still very tasty.
I have no words to say about Rise Bakery
The BEST cinnamon rolls I ever had!!
The gluten free bread is fantastic!

I have NEVER written a review but this place was awful!!! As someone who can’t eat gluten, I was uber excited to try out this place. Unfortunately, my experience left me wishing I had never stepped foot in Rise Bakery or had even supported this business. Firstly, there’s no prices anywhere! Of course they have $3.50 cupcakes labeled but that’s it! Even the to-go menu didn’t have prices! When I asked the woman at the register how much the sandwiches were she didn’t know either and had to ring up each individual sandwich. After finding out a ham and cheese by itself was $10.50 I didn’t even want a sandwich anymore (and I’m glad I didn’t). Now I decide to order a cupcake because if I didn’t like it, at least I was only loosing $3.50... let me just say that cupcake was SO dry... Rise Bakery should be called Sand Bakery because that cupcake tasted like cold sand. I’m my opinion, they put no effort in make those cupcakes... maybe all there effort went into making their $10.50 sandwiches. Needless to say, I walked away highly disappointed and very sad that a place for gluten free people was selling terrible products. I’ve had better from the grocery store...
Had an excellent turkey pesto sandwich and carrot cake cupcake. I would totally come back.
My girlfriend said it was the best croissant of her life.

I’ve been gluten free for 7 years and in that time I had never found a flakey, buttery, delicious gluten free croissant. But Rise has it! Not only do they have a plain croissant, they also have chocolate croissants and so many other amazing looking gluten free treats! Truly the BEST!!
Excellent source of gluten free, dairy free, egg free yumminess
Fantastic Cinnamon Rolls :)

Made a special trip just to Rise gluten-free bakery. I am Celiac and my husband is a good sport. Both of us thoroughly enjoyed our breakfast sandwiches. I got the Bacon Egg & Cheese on a Ham & Cheese Croissant. Tasted like the real thing. My husband had the Bacon Egg & Cheese on a biscuit and enjoyed his as well. We are headed home with a 6-pack of Everything Bagels and a 6-pack of Chocolate Chip cookies to enjoy this week. Highly recommend!
Fantastic vegan chocolate chip cookies!
This bakery is amazing! So happy to discover it. The cupcakes are delicious, and the ham & cheese croissant is to die for!

We live in the northern edge of Silver Spring and it’s so worth driving into DC for their GF (gluten free) baked goods. Quite possibly the BEST GF carrot cake I had. Wonderful GF bake shop, and definitely worth the trek into DC.

My wife is Celiac. Gluten is not a fad diet for her. She bought bagels, muffins, cinnamon rolls & cookies. I tried them & they were excellent. Unfortunately we flew from St. Louis to DC to get it lol (business trip & we discovered literally hours before heading to airport to come home) she stocked up & spent the next week eating the goodies.
Delicious gluten free baked goods and a friendly staff make this place a must for people with food allergies. The coffee is great too! We'll work the trip.
Delicious gluten free cupcakes and biscuits! Yum!
Gluten-free done right! Delicious treats and healthy breads too. Everything is gluten free and there are other allergen-free options too. Not too much seating, but it usually works out.

We happened upon this fantastic gluten-free bakery near the National Zoo, due to a mention on one of the maps. We just had to check it out, even though it was a few blocks from out destination. We were not disappointed that we did!  The AGM was very friendly and knowledgeable, and the gluten-free goodies we got were fantastic!  It's always a nice surprise to run across a gluten-free shop and enjoy what they have to offer to boot. Great find and if you are in DC, you must check it out!
The best gluten free facility that we have found in DC.
Delicious!
Amazing goodies!!! Worth the drive from Timonium
All gluten free products.

We are here visiting and our home city has only a few options for gluten-free baked goods. Everything we ordered was delicious - biscuits, breakfast bagel, eclair, chocolate croissant - they do a great job!
I was there to pickup gluten free morning pastries for some co-workers and I've never heard so many positive adjectives to describe a simple everything bagel. Very nice and helpful folks.
Great cozy place for morning breakfast.
Best GF friendly place in the STATE!  cake or frozen goods to go, hot sammich to stay.  Love these folks so much!  I'll never pass through LR without stopping here.

I love Rise.  As far as I know they are the only dedicated gluten free bakery within DC.  The cinnamon rolls, cakes, cupcakes and breads - I am a repeat customer for all of them! Recently I had a mistake with an order and they were excellent in helping me get things right.  I’m impressed with their products and their staff.
Yum yum yum! Can I move in next door?!
Great little gluten free bakery with breakfast and lunch options.  Had bacon and cheese on GF biscuit plus grabbed a chocolate croissant!

Rise Bakery is my happy place . I've been a constant customer at their place and love all of their cakes. Not only the cakes of Rise Bakery are amazing , but also the other stuff that they sell is delicious. I've taken cakes for many occasions from them and every time , the taste was equally good. This place never disappoints you.
Great gluten free bakery! I'm don't have to eat gluten free but someone I love does and I couldn't even tell I was eating a gf cupcake. It was great! Highly recommend
Everything gluten free!

If you have a Gluten intolerance this is a great place to visit. My wife has coeliac's and we read about this place. Took us 45mins to get there from our hotel but was worth the trip. The choice was fantastic. Service was quick, they even had a wee table and chairs so we could sit in. The cakes/brownies were fantastic was so hard to choose what to pick we eneded up taking cookies home.
Wow. Great breakfast options - get the cinnamon roll!
The food was good albeit expensive. I was just so happy there was a gluten free bakery. I suggest getting the cupcakes.
Delicious gluten free pastry. Only two tables for seating
Very tasty. No gluten but also options with no dairy, soy, egg, or nuts. Two little tables if you would like to eat there.
Great little shop to grab a sandwich! Very nice staff!
Best gluten free bakery in DC! They even have lunch options! I always try and catch thier farmers market on Wednesdays at Foggy bottom to get my weekly supply of bread and cookies 🌈

Our family luvs the Rise Bakery!!!!   After finding out our daughter needed to eat gluten free we were in search of amazing pastry/breakfast items.  We were sooo grateful to stumble upon Rise during a morning bike ride in Adams Morgan.  Everything we have tried has been amazing.  Sometimes after school we treat some of my daughters’ friends & their parents (who are not GF) and they also thought it was sooooo delicious!  Couple that with a cool & friendly staff makes it a 5 star business!
Best gluten free bakery around

I absolutely love this place. The bagels are amazing and the sandwiches are great too. Not only is everything gluten free, but it actually tastes like real, normal food. It's a bit pricey (but when is GF stuff not pricey?) but you are paying for the quality as well.  The only downside is that the few times I've been in recently, the customer service has not been great. I get that it's a small, busy place, but it's pretty awkward being ignored for the first 5 mins before someone takes my order. If staff could at least acknowledge people when they come in, that would go a long way.

It’s ok. The avocado toast is the only vegan breakfast meal option; it is good but it’s tiny. They have vegan cream cheese for a non-vegan bagel for their customers who want to eat dairy free (which makes 0 sense)
Excellent,  everything sold is  gluten free
Extremely delicious gluten free bakery
Great place to eat. Lots of choices and friendly staff.Simon(England)

Love it! My boyfriend decided to take me one Saturday morning when they first opened and there was already a line! I had been complaining about lack or breads, croissants, ect to have for breakfast. Low and behold here comes Rise Bakery!  They have best ham and cheese croissant I have ever had. Fast, reasonably priced and all within walking distance of my job.  I cannot wait to see the growth that comes from this place. Keep up the good work!
Awesome food. Everything is Gluten Free and tastes  amazing. Some of the best gluten free bread ever.
They keep a very low inventory, leaving disappointingly few options available for on site purchase.  Call ahead calls unanswered, website down to email.  Say too much demand.
Great food but very slow service, staff were standing around talking to each other while a queue grew. Unfortunate for a shop catering to a morning, so folks likely en route to work, crowd.
Loved this bakery the moment I found it. The staff is wonderful and friendly. The Owner and the Bakers are passionate about their food.

This place is AMAZING. It turned out that my other allergies (besides gluten) made it so that there was only one thing I could order. (FYI: There are traces of corn and yeast in almost everything they make.) But the staff was so nice! They went through their whole menu with me, trying to help me find something I could eat. Then when I went back several days later, they remembered me. Even though I can only order their cinnamon roll, I'll go back again and again.

We loved all the gluten free options.  We tired the cherry cookies, banana bread, cinnamon roll, bagel sandwich and coffee.  Everything was delicious and my kid loved the cookies!!!  Some items were also egg free, dairy free.  Would visit again for sure on future trips to DC.

Everything here is delicious.  As someone with Celiac disease, it was refreshing to be able to order anything off the menu and know it was safe.  It's been awhile since I've had croissants or buiscuits.  Hard not to buy everything all at once. 😊
Gluten free
Completely gluten free! Also offering nut free, dairy free, and vegan options. Great sandwiches and baked goods.
Tasty pastry. Need more counter help as no one helped a few of us for some time and they were not visible to greet anyone.

I ordered a BLT, chocolate cupcake, and the Nutella brownie. Let me just say if you have gluten allergies this is the perfect place for you. The BLT was so delicious I would eat it even if I wasn't gluten-free. It's the first sandwich I've eat you that did not make me sick or feel some kind of bad.
Very tasty gluten free stuff😋
Cinnamon rolls are the best gluten free ones we ever had. Helpful employees. They deliver to quite a few restaurants in DC as well.
Eclair
Delicious food and coffee, awesome Adams Morgan location, and kind and swift staff. I will definitely come back on my next DC visit!
This 1 star review is for the service, I’ve not tried the baked goods yet. The cashier was incredibly rude. She straight up lied to my face when I asked about my order.
Perfect bakery for people with Celiac! 😙  100% gluten free and very delicious 🤗

So delicious and so much variety! I may eat all my meals here. I'm thrilled to have a place where I can get a gluten free sandwich and feel satisfied. Plus I can be confident that there won't be any cross-contamination which is huge as a person with celiac disease. THANK YOU!
This one has lemon poppy seed muffins!
Amazing gluten free bakery with crave-inducing croissants. Swings coffee and great staff. What else is there?
Great atmosphere and cozy setting for a cup of tea
Love, love, LOVE the products here! Recently found out about this bakery and now I'm obsessed with their GF bread 🍞 been slowly trying all the pastries too, hehe, and the cheesecake is to die for!
I love this place! It is amazing to be able to find all your favorite treats without gluten. I highly recommend. I mean cmon they have a GF bagel!!!!

This is the type of bakery I had been searching for. The gluten-free croissants are one of a kind and they make fresh gluten-free brioche, sourdough and gluten-free breakfast sandwiches. It gets crowded, especially on weekends but you can usually find a seat on weekdays.  They have a pretty wide variety of sweets and pastries (I'd recommend the eclair and the cinnamon roll), but I've been most impressed with the variety and the quality of the bread. They make a lot of it fresh every day and they also keep additional breads, bagels and croissants stocked frozen.  Overall, I'd say it's the best gluten-free bakery I've ever been to. A close second would be Noglu in Paris. Rise is the cream of the crop in the good ol' USA!
This place is just basic. With basic service and basic food. Not a place I’d recommend highly to anyone. You guys should really work on your customer service.

All right, let me just start by saying that having a gluten allergy and worrying about everything you consume sucks. This place is 100% gluten free and a true gem! Everything is delicious and safe to eat. The sandwich I had for lunch was outstanding and the bread was perfect! The sweets are great too and I will most definitely some back. The space is small and there are only two tables, just something to be aware if your planning to eat there. The staff was great too.
Really delicious, and I'm saying that as someone who can eat gluten! Get the BLT or the biscuits, they're so so good. The croissants are a little heavy but they're still good.
Best gluten free bakery I have ever been to. You have to try everything!
The bagels and breads are amazing. Great quality gluten free breads.

Great quick stop for anyone looking for a Gluten free snack and a coffee. They cater to multiple dietary choices (egg free, nut free etc) their pastries looked tremendous. We had their egg, cheese and bacon bagels with a chocolate croissant and it was top notch 👌🏻 Bagels sure were a bit wee but they were smashing regardless, and that croissant was cracking 👍🏻
For a gluten free baking option.

This was such a lovely, cute bakery! It's so nice to have a fully gluten-free and allergy-conscious bakery (they mark nut- and soy-free items too) . The staff were incredibly nice and there was a great selection of sweet and savory items.  Additionally, they sell loaves if bread and frozen loafs too!
First time taking my daughter to a Gluten-free bakery. Not only was a food delicious, the people were helpful and sweet. Wish we had one closer to home!
My poor husband walked 1.5 miles in the rain to get this for me. I haven’t had a bagel in years. It was glorious!
Amazing gluten free breakfast treats as well as sandwiches for lunch! Expertly made coffee as well, a definite must-go when in AdMo!
Excellent service; best gluten free bread products in the city. Hit the bagels and croissants!!!!!!

Found this place online, just moved to DC and Im absolutely IN LOVE. Outstanding gluten free goods, never had anything like it. Prices are definitely ok considering DC and considering GF. Completely worth it. Will be coming back on the regular now! Just awesome.

My girlfriend recently found out that she is allergic to gluten, so when we found Rise, we were thrilled. Their products are delicious and don't betray their gluten-free nature easily. Best of all, their staff is friendly and prompt, so we always feel welcome there. My favorite is their breakfast sammie on an everything bagel, but the pumpkin cranberry bread is also a definite winner. We occasionally bring Rise baked goods with us when we visit friends or family and we always have success. Thank you Rise for making gluten-free a lot easier!
Nice food and ladies
Eclair was expensive and the service was slow. The food was OK but not great.
Excellent gluten free bakery

Really wanted to like this place. Came here twice: The first time was for a bagel sandwich. I waited for over 20 minutes and they had lost my order, so I had to re-order and wait even longer. Then, for a party at work, I ordered a blueberry pie by phone three days ahead of time. When I came to collect, they had given the pie to someone else! Later they called to say the person brought it back, but by then I was in my VA office. Won't try a third time.
Always friendly and welcoming! I especially love their ham and cheese croissant!
Lots of great vegan and gluten free options. Their superfood bread is delicious, so are their desserts! Stopped by for lunch and had their vegan caprese sandwich, loved it.
Vegan chocolate chip cookies are to die for

I found Rise online when searching for baked goods for a baby shower tea I was giving for my gluten intolerant daughter. Jackpot!  The Rise bagels, croissants, and brioche made tea sandwiches so good that wheat eating guests may become converts to gluten free. The Rise gluten-free scones were biggest hit -- gingery sweet in taste, creamy crumb texture--a real treat. I arranged a pre-order and it was boxed perfectly and ready to go for pickup on the morning of the shower.  Mike and colleagues are great to work with. For those of us who live outside Adams Morgan, Rise is definitely not a cinch to get to, but well worth the effort. If you're  walking or hanging out on 18th Street don't walk by.  Walk up the stairs and go try something on their excellent menu.
Croissants are the BEST!
Staff was great and really helpful, they label every thing with common allergens so it was easy to find something safe.
Nice all-gluten-free place with some vegan items
Excellent eclairs!
Good gluten cup cakes

This isn't just a gluten free bakery, it's a gluten free bakery with the most outstanding selection of any I've seen outside of New York and Portland, Maine. Cinnamon Rolls, chocolate croissant, ham and cheese croissant, eclairs, breakfast muffins, as well as the standard brownie and cupcakes. Also available are frozen bread and frozen biscuits (USA style). The eclair and croissants were outstanding, as was the cinnamon roll. Not just made well, but using a bespoke recipe to achieve a better taste then a typical gluten free recipe manages.

Friendly service, they certainly didn't judge that I was trying to buy up all the goodies. It was my first time there, and my first time in a bakery since being told by my doctor to stay away from gluten. I was in heaven, even before I tasted it, but the taste , goodness...is amazing, better than what most gluten laden sweets and baked goods taste like. I think I tried everything, and EVERYTHING was good! The superfood bread needs to be a staple in my house, the vegan chocolate chip cookies are to die for and the everything bagel, cinnamon roll and red velvet cupcake...was all worth the drive all the way there from where I live. I'll be on my treadmill until I return :-)
Awesome place to grab breakfast, or just a quick pastry wether you're a gluten free eater or not.
Very happy to have found this gem of a gluten free bakery :-). The croissants are super tasty and there's lots of other restricted diet options!

I am new to the whole gluten free lifestyle I found Rise Bakery on the internet and with all the great reviews I decided to try. I was not disappointed. The chocolate chip cookies, the ham and cheese croissants are so delicious. Looking forward to trying to challah bread!

This place is like heaven for those of us who have had to give up anything gluten-filled due to allergies. I have been craving an "everything bagel" loaded with cream cheese for YEARS and my craving was FINALLY satisfied here!!! I wish I could give this place more than 5 stars! It's just SO good! The croissants are great too, just keep in mind you won't get that same flakey texture (because you need gluten for that) but they are an excellent replacement for "real" croissants! I haven't even made it to the sweets counter yet.... That's for another trip. For now, I have bagel to shove in my face, so gotta go

Very good gluten free baked goods! Including the items you loved when you were glutenous and have missed dearly i.e. Sticky cinnamon rolls and croissants!  Get them warmed if offered. You can still see the buttery layers in the croissants. Delicious. A must for the gluten free folk!  Plus they have almond milk on the counter for those who don't take dairy/soy in their coffee. Always nice to see!

Excellent gluten free baked goods! The cinnamon rolls and eclairs are amazing! We took home a loaf of frozen bread and it's the closest consistency to non-GF bread we've ever seen. Would highly recommend if you have Celiac or severe gluten sensitivity. Even if you're not GF (my wife is but I'm not), their food is worth a visit.
Great tasting cakes and very good bread options. Very good coffee as well.

The bagels and biscuits are great! The chocolate croissant I had was good, but it didn't really have the texture of a croissant. I also had a "cupcake" that was really more like a muffin (very dense). In addition to GF, they also have options for people with other food sensitivities.
It has great gluten free cinnamon buns!

My experience with Rise Bakery began after trying to purchase a gluten free birthday cake for a "gluten free" friend's birthday. You need to place an order 48 hours in advance to get a cake which seems a little ridonculous so I ended up getting cupcakes instead, the order was not correct so the manager offered his apologies and a 50% discount which definitely made me like the place a lot.  As far as the cupcakes go, after taking a small bite of the red velvet cupcake, my knees became weak and I started hallucinating that I was riding on a unicorn through rainbow land and swimming through that incredibly delicious cream cheese topping. Apparently, a few minutes later I came to, on the floor; everyone was staring at me and I had satisfied look on my face which warranted a cigarette; except, I don't smoke. It was only then that I realized that my oral euphoric orgasm was caused by rise bakery's use of magical elf crack, which they stir in a cauldron stolen from Harry Potter himself and sprinkled on their cupcakes using fairy dust from neverland while holding an infinity stone. I have been craving those cupcakes ever since. Thank you Rise Bakery for your delicious cupcakes, and I hate you for making me addicted. ;)
Many and tasty gluten free options. A nice little place in the nice neighborhood

I hadn't had a croissant in 5 years, and theirs were buttery and delicious (admittedly not quite the same as their glutenous brothers, but somehow the mouthfeel is the same!). I was also very impressed with the brioche rolls and biscuits I took home from the freezer section! I'll be back for sure.
LOVE this bakery. everything is gluten free and it never disappoints. the bread is so fresh too

We hosted a Bat Mitzvah at Cesco Osteria in Bethesda this weekend  and did an all gluten-free menu for the client.  We called Rise Bakery and they were wonderful.  The challah was the best I have ever tasted.  I will certainly recommend clients for future events.    We have several weddings coming up that require a gluten-free menu.  We will be back.
Devil's Food Cake was awesome! Thanks for accommodating on such short notice. Will come back

I am gluten-free not by choice and am always in search of good gluten-free bakeries. I went to this bakery at after hearing all the fuss and seeing the great reviews however was disappointed. I got a chocolate croissant, chocolate cupcake and bag of 4 plain bagels. Not trying to be a negative Nancy but none of it was good. The croissant was extremely dense and tasted nothing like a croissant, the bagels too were extremely dense and I struggled to eat just 1/2 of the bagel and the cupcake, frankly I've made gluten-free cupcakes that taste better. Also, while I am use the the higher cost of gluten-free items, I spent over $20 for the 3 items and ended up throwing it all away after a few bites.  Maybe my taste buds are different but I've had better free gluten free bakery items. I personally would not recommend this bakery to any of my  colleagues, friends or family. Just my opinion. Maybe they had a bad batch or bad day, regardless, I won't be wasting my money again. People like what they like so if you like then continue to enjoy. If you have never been then I recommend proceeding with caution and venturing there only if you truly have money to throw away.
Great gluten free bakery

This bakery has small items at overall expensive prices.  Dough used for ham & cheese, and chocolate croissants is very tasty although not very croissant- like.  (Maybe using the dough for popovers would be better.) However, chocolate, and ham & cheese filling was too little for the amount of dough.  Everything bagels are very small and at $8.95 for four too expensive, especially since they taste very dry and somewhat sandy.  My friend had a chocolate cupcake which she really enjoyed.
SO MANY GLUTEN FREE OPTIONS HERE!

I tried this place once so far and was very impressed.  They have a big sign pointing out that the whole bakery is gluten free, which put my mom and me at ease.  And the croissants were amazing.  I hadn't had one in years because of my gluten free lifestyle and these were exactly how I remembered them being.  I can't wait to go back and try their other baked goods!
Disappointed. Didnt like bread or bagel
The first croissant and turnover I have had in 10 years. Definitely worth the wait! The bagels are wonderful as are the cupcakes. It is gluten free heaven!

The plain, chocolate and ham & cheese croissants were all delicious! Also bought some biscuits that were frozen to take for home. All around great experience and lots of options. Definitely a place to visit!
As I vegan I appreciate gluten free items not tasting "gluten free"! Their food is amazing!!

My friend and I randomly stopped here and after getting a sample of the nutella brownie, just had to bring one home to my boyfriend, who loved it. We also tried the almond croissant, which was as good as any croissant with gluten in it! Will definitely come back here!

First, the fresh-from-the-oven chocolate croissant made me tear up it was so good. I've REALLY missed croissants since having to go GF, and this made the 5-year wait worth every second. The regular croissant was also amazing! Wish they had a branch in Bethesda!
They're amazing, but they're never open. I would buy a lot more of their goods if they were open later/on weekdays again.
This bakery is so good! I just wish they'd change their hours and open earlier, so I can grab something on my way to work!

Finally tried the gluten-free croissant which was perfect. There were lots of vegan bakery options too for my boyfriend (who isn't gluten-free, but enjoyed his gluten-free cupcake.)  They have some of the best gluten-free bread too -- sub buns, rolls.  I stop by for a bagel w/ cream cheese at least once a week. It's a great spot with a cozy seating section and friendly staff.
